revision.text:
{{grading}} In [[Egypt]] the [[academic]] [[grading (education)|grading system]] functions with a worded grade and increases in increments from 30-10 points.
The title ''gayyid giddan'' or very good denotes the second highest mark possible, on par with a "B" student.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aucegypt.edu/academic/gradstudies/categories.htm |title=Graduate admissions |publisher=The American University in Cairo |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080906151723/http://www.aucegypt.edu/academic/gradstudies/categories.htm |archivedate=2008-09-06 }}</ref> {|class="wikitable" !Percent !Qualification |- ! 85–100 |Excellent (Momtaz) ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: {{rtl-lang|ar|ممتاز}}) |- ! 75–84 |Very good or Distinct (Gayed Gedan) (Arabic: {{rtl-lang|ar|جيد جدًا}}) |- ! 65–74 |Good (Gayed) or credit(Arabic: {{rtl-lang|ar|جيد}}) |- ! 50–64 |Acceptable (Maqboul)or pass (Arabic: {{rtl-lang|ar|مقبول}}) |- ! 30–49 |Weak (Daeef) (Arabic: {{rtl-lang|ar|ضعيف}}) |- ! 0–29 |Very weak (Daeef Gedan) (Arabic: {{rtl-lang|ar|ضعيف جدًا}}) |}
