{{Infobox university |name = Airbus Training Centre Europe |image_size = |motto = |established = |type = Type Rating Training Organization |endowment = |chancellor = |vice_chancellor = |students = |city = [[Blagnac]] |country = {{FRA}} |campus = | former_names = |colours = |nickname = |mascot = |website = [http://www.aircraft.airbus.com/support-services/services/training/training-centers-network/airbus-training-centre-europe-toulouse/ Airbus Training Centre Europe] |image_name = |partner = |affiliations = [[International Association of Aviation Personnel Schools]] }}
'''Airbus Training Centre Europe''' is one of the eight centres of the European aerospace company [[Airbus]] dedicated to airline pilot and engineer training<ref>[https://aviationvoice.com/which-aviation-training-centre-in-europe-was-voted-the-best-201702241750/ Which Aviation Training Centre in Europe Was Voted the Best?]</ref>. Located at [[Blagnac]], close to [[Toulouse]] (France), the centre is approved by [[civil aviation authority]] to deliver courses on [[Airbus A300]], [[Airbus A310|A310]], [[Airbus A320 family|A320 family]], [[Airbus A330|A330]], [[Airbus A340|A340]], [[Airbus A350 XWB|A350XWB]] and [[Airbus A380|A380]].
The centre is equipped with six [[full flight simulator]]s.
Airbus also has training centres in [[Hamburg]], [[Miami]], [[Beijing]], [[Singapore]], [[Bangalore]], [[New Delhi]]<ref>[https://www.pilotcareernews.com/airbus-pilot-training-delhi/ Airbus to open pilot training centre in Delhi]</ref> and [[Mexico]].
