[[Image:Marcipangris.jpg|thumb|A [[marzipan pig]], an example of a typical "almond present".]]
An '''almond present''' ({{lang-da|mandelgave}}, {{lang-no|mandelgave}}, {{lang-is|möndlugjöf}}, {{lang-sv|mandelgåva}}) is a small present traditionally given in some [[Nordic countries]] to the person who gets the whole [[almond]] put in the [[rice pudding]] served for [[Christmas]].

The tradition may originate from the somewhat similar [[king cake]] tradition on [[Epiphany (holiday)|Epiphany]], observed in, e.g., France.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mandelgave |url=http://www.biblioteksvagten.dk/videnbase_svar.asp?qaid=15561 |date=22 August 2007 |work= |publisher=Biblioteksvagten.dk |language=Danish |accessdate=24 August 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071222182309/http://www.biblioteksvagten.dk/videnbase_svar.asp?qaid=15561 |archive-date=2007-12-22 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

