{{Infobox recurring event | name = Bluedot | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = Lovell_Telescope.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = bluedot takes place against the backdrop of the [[Lovell Telescope]] at [[Jodrell Bank Observatory]] (JBO) in Cheshire | status = Active | genre = [[Music festival]], [[Science festival]] | frequency = Annual | location = [[Jodrell Bank Observatory]], [[Cheshire]], United Kingdom | coordinates = | years_active = | first = {{start date|2016|07|22}} | founder_name = | last = {{start date|2018|07|20}} | next = {{start date|2019|07|18}} | participants = | attendance = 15000 per day<ref name=bd/> | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = | website = {{URL|discoverthebluedot.com}} | footnotes = }}
'''Bluedot''' is a music, science and culture event held annually in July since 2016 at [[Jodrell Bank Observatory]] in [[Cheshire]], England, combining music, live science experiments, expert talks and immersive artworks.<ref name=bd>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/|title=Bluedot|website=Bluedot}}</ref><ref name=men>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/bluedot-festival-2017-review-saturday-13304102|title=Review: Bluedot Festival day two at Jodrell Bank|publisher=[[Manchester Evening News]]|website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk|first=Emily|last=Heward|year=2017}}</ref><ref name=guardian>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/jul/24/bluedot-festival-review-jodrell-bank-observatory-underworld-jean-michel-jarre|first=Daniel|last=Martin|year=2016|title=Bluedot festival review – cosmic vibes permeate rave revival|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|website=theguardian.com}}</ref>
[[File:Pale Blue Dot.png|thumb|upright=0.8|alt=Dark grey and black static with coloured vertical rays of sunlight over part of the image. A small pale blue point of light is barely visible.|The ''[[Pale Blue Dot]]'' photograph]] The festival is named after ''[[Pale Blue Dot]]'', a famous photograph of planet Earth popularised by [[Carl Sagan]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Carl|last=Sagan|year=1990|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wupToqz1e2g|website=youtube.com|title=The Pale Blue Dot|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>
==Musical performances== Since 2016, acts performing at the bluedot festival have included [[New Order (band)|New Order]], [[Orbital (band)|Orbital]], [[Underworld (band)|Underworld]], [[Alt-J]], [[Goldfrapp]], [[Jean-Michel Jarre]],<ref name=bd/><ref name=men/><ref name=guardian/> [[The Chemical Brothers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theskinny.co.uk/music/live-music/reviews/bluedot-festival-2018-review|title=Bluedot Festival 2018: Review - The Skinny|publisher=}}</ref> [[Gary Numan]], [[Hot Chip]] and [[The Flaming Lips]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jul/23/bluedot-festival-review-gary-numan-flaming-lips|title=Bluedot festival review – Gary Numan makes waves at science-pop mashup|first=Daniel Dylan|last=Wray|date=23 July 2018|website=the Guardian}}</ref> [[Kraftwerk]] are to headline Saturday at the 2019 event.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/kraftwerk-headline-bluedot-2019-festival-2404790|title=Kraftwerk announce huge 2019 UK festival show as Bluedot headliners|date=2018-11-21|accessdate=2018-11-27|first=Sam|last=Moore}}</ref>
==Science talks== The festival has included talks and demonstrations from [[Richard Dawkins]], [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]], [[Jim Al-Khalili]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/science-in-the-soul:-richard-dawkins-in-conversation-with-jim-al-khali|title=Science In The Soul: Richard Dawkins in Conversation with Jim Al-Khalili – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref> [[Philippa Browning]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/philippa-browning-1|title=Philippa Browning – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref> [[Timothy John O'Brien]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/tim-o'brien-1|title=Tim O'Brien – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref> [[Sarah Bridle]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/sarah-bridle|title=Sarah Bridle – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref> [[Lisa Harvey-Smith]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/lisa-harvey-smith-|title=Lisa Harvey-Smith – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref> and [[Teresa Anderson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/profile/teresa-anderson-1|title=Teresa Anderson – Bluedot Festival|website=Bluedot Festival}}</ref>
