{{Infobox language |name = Loosduinen dialect |nativename = Loosduins |pronunciation = {{IPA|[loʊ̯zˈdœy̯ns]}} |states = [[Netherlands]] |region = [[The Hague]] |speakers =? |ref = |familycolor = Indo-European |fam1 = [[Germanic languages|Germanic]] |fam2=[[West Germanic languages|West Germanic]] |fam3=[[Low Franconian languages|Low Franconian]] |fam4=[[Dutch language|Dutch]] |fam5=[[Hollandic dialect]] |fam6=[[South Hollandic]] |isoexception=dialect |glotto=none }}
'''Loosduinen dialect''' is a [[dialect]] of [[Dutch language|Dutch]] spoken in the [[Loosduinen]] district of [[The Hague]]. It is very similar to [[The Hague dialect]].{{sfnp|Goeman|1999}}
== Notable people == * [[Koos Meinderts]] (writer)
